{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":0,"text":"I'd like to speak about technology trends,"},{"time":4000,"text":"which is something that many of you follow --"},{"time":8000,"text":"but we also follow, for related reasons."},{"time":12000,"text":"Obviously, being a technology magazine, technology trends"},{"time":15000,"text":"are something that we write about and need to know about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":19000,"text":"But also it's part of being any monthly magazine --"},{"time":22000,"text":"you live in the future. And we have a long lead-time."},{"time":25000,"text":"We have to plan issues many months in advance;"},{"time":27000,"text":"we have to guess at what public appetites are going to be six months,"},{"time":30000,"text":"nine months down the road. So we're in the forecasting business."}]},{"cues":[{"time":35000,"text":"We also, like a lot of companies, create a product"},{"time":37000,"text":"that's based on technology trends."},{"time":38000,"text":"In this case, ours is about ideas and information, and, if we're lucky,"},{"time":43000,"text":"some entertainment. But the concept's quite the same."},{"time":47000,"text":"And so we have to understand"},{"time":49000,"text":"not only why tech's important, where it's going,"},{"time":51000,"text":"but also, very importantly, when -- the timing is everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":57000,"text":"And it's interesting, when you look at the predictions made"},{"time":61000,"text":"during the peak of the boom in the 1990s, about e-commerce,"},{"time":66000,"text":"or Internet traffic, or broadband adoption, or Internet advertising,"},{"time":71000,"text":"they were all right -- they were just wrong in time."},{"time":75000,"text":"Almost every one of those has come true just a few years later."},{"time":78000,"text":"But the difference of a few years on stock-market valuations"},{"time":82000,"text":"is obviously extreme. And that's why timing is everything."}]},{"cues":[{"time":87000,"text":"You've probably seen something like this before."},{"time":89000,"text":"This is the classic Gartner Hype Curve, which talks about"},{"time":91000,"text":"kind of the trajectory of a technology's lifespan."},{"time":94000,"text":"And just for fun, we put a bunch of technologies on it,"},{"time":96000,"text":"to show whether they were kind of rising for the first high peak,"},{"time":100000,"text":"or whether they were about to crash"},{"time":101000,"text":"into the trough of disillusionment,"},{"time":104000,"text":"or rise back in the slope of enlightenment, etc."},{"time":109000,"text":"And this is one way to do technology forecasting: get a sense"},{"time":112000,"text":"of where technology is and then anticipate the next upturn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":116000,"text":"We tend to do any technology that we think is sufficiently important;"},{"time":119000,"text":"we'll typically do it twice. Once, we want to do it first."},{"time":123000,"text":"We want to be the first to do it, for the geeks who appreciate that,"},{"time":126000,"text":"we'll catch it right there at the technology-trigger."},{"time":128000,"text":"You can see in 1997, we put Linux on the cover."},{"time":132000,"text":"But then it comes back. And sufficiently big technologies"},{"time":136000,"text":"are going to hit the mainstream, and they're going to burst out."},{"time":138000,"text":"And then it's time to do it again. Last year."},{"time":143000,"text":"And that's one way that we try to time technology trends."}]},{"cues":[{"time":147000,"text":"I'd like to talk about a way of thinking about technology trends"},{"time":150000,"text":"that I call my \"grand unified theory of predicting the future,\""},{"time":154000,"text":"but it's closer to a petite unified theory of predicting the future."},{"time":160000,"text":"It's based on the presumption, the observation even,"},{"time":163000,"text":"that all important technologies go through four stages in their life --"},{"time":168000,"text":"at least one of the four stages, sometimes all four of the stages."},{"time":172000,"text":"And at each one of these stages, can be seen as a collision --"},{"time":177000,"text":"a collision with something else --"},{"time":180000,"text":"for example, a critical price-line that changes both the technology"},{"time":184000,"text":"and also changes its effect on the world. It's an inflection point."},{"time":188000,"text":"And these are the inflection points that tell you"},{"time":191000,"text":"what the next chapter in that technology's life is going to be,"},{"time":195000,"text":"and maybe how you can do something about it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":199000,"text":"The first is the critical price."},{"time":201000,"text":"The first stage in a technology's advance"},{"time":203000,"text":"is that it'll fall below a critical price."},{"time":207000,"text":"After it falls below a critical price, it will tend,"},{"time":209000,"text":"if it's successful, to rise above a critical mass, a penetration."},{"time":214000,"text":"Many technologies, at that point, displace another technology,"},{"time":220000,"text":"and that's another important point."},{"time":224000,"text":"And then finally, a lot of technologies commoditize."},{"time":227000,"text":"Towards the end of their life, they become nearly free."}]},{"cues":[{"time":230000,"text":"Each one of those is an opportunity to do something about it;"},{"time":233000,"text":"it's an opportunity for the technology to change."},{"time":235000,"text":"And even if you missed, you know, the first boom of Wi-Fi --"},{"time":239000,"text":"you know, Wi-Fi did the critical price, it did the critical mass,"},{"time":243000,"text":"but hasn't done displacement yet, and hasn't done free yet --"},{"time":246000,"text":"there's still more opportunity in that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":248000,"text":"I'd like to demonstrate what I mean by this"},{"time":250000,"text":"by telling the story of the DVD,"},{"time":252000,"text":"which is a technology which has done all of these."},{"time":255000,"text":"The DVD, as you know, was introduced in the mid-1990s"},{"time":258000,"text":"and it was quite expensive. But you can see that by 1998,"},{"time":263000,"text":"it had fallen below 400 dollars, and 400 dollars was a psychological threshold."},{"time":268000,"text":"And it started to take off. And you can see that the units"},{"time":272000,"text":"started to trend up, the hidden inflection point -- it was taking off."}]},{"cues":[{"time":278000,"text":"The next thing it hit, a year later, was critical mass. In this case,"},{"time":283000,"text":"20 percent is often a good proxy for critical mass in a household."},{"time":287000,"text":"And what's interesting here"},{"time":289000,"text":"is that something else took off along with it: home-theater units."},{"time":294000,"text":"Suddenly you have a DVD in the house;"},{"time":296000,"text":"you've got high-quality digital video;"},{"time":298000,"text":"you have a reason to have a big-screen television;"},{"time":300000,"text":"you have a reason for Dolby 5.1 surround-sound."},{"time":304000,"text":"And maybe you have reasons for starting to connect them,"},{"time":306000,"text":"and bring the rest of your entertainment in."},{"time":308000,"text":"What's interesting also is -- note that Netflix was founded in 1999."},{"time":312000,"text":"Reed Hastings is here. He clearly saw that that was a moment,"},{"time":317000,"text":"that was an inflection point that he could do something with."}]},{"cues":[{"time":321000,"text":"The next phase it hit was displacement."},{"time":323000,"text":"You can see around 2001 it finally out-sold the VCR."},{"time":327000,"text":"And here too, you can see the implications in the world at large."},{"time":333000,"text":"Netflix was right -- the Netflix model could capitalize on the DVD"},{"time":337000,"text":"in a way that the video-rental stores couldn't."},{"time":340000,"text":"Among the DVD's many assets is that it's very small;"},{"time":343000,"text":"you can stick it in the mailer and post it cheaply."},{"time":346000,"text":"That gave an advantage; that was an implication"},{"time":350000,"text":"of the technology's rise that wasn't obvious to everybody."}]},{"cues":[{"time":354000,"text":"And then finally, DVDs are approaching free."},{"time":357000,"text":"There's a company called Apex, a no-name Chinese firm,"},{"time":359000,"text":"who has, several times in the past year, been the number-one"},{"time":363000,"text":"DVD seller in America. Their average price, for last year, was 48 dollars."},{"time":370000,"text":"You're aware of the"},{"time":372000,"text":"perhaps apocryphal Wal-Mart stampede"},{"time":376000,"text":"over the 30-dollar DVD."},{"time":380000,"text":"But they're getting very, very cheap,"},{"time":382000,"text":"and look at the interesting implication of it. As they get cheaper,"},{"time":386000,"text":"the premium brands, the Sonys and such, are losing market share,"},{"time":389000,"text":"and the no-names, the Apexes, are gaining them."},{"time":391000,"text":"They're being commodified, and that's what happens"},{"time":393000,"text":"when things go to zero. It's a tough market out there."},{"time":398000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":401000,"text":"Now they've introduced these four ways of looking at technology,"},{"time":404000,"text":"these four stages of technology's life."},{"time":406000,"text":"I'd like to talk about some other technologies out there,"},{"time":409000,"text":"just technologies on our radar -- and I'll use this lens,"},{"time":412000,"text":"these four, as a way to kind of tell you"},{"time":414000,"text":"where each one of those technologies is in its development."},{"time":417000,"text":"They're not necessarily the top-10 technologies out there --"},{"time":420000,"text":"they're just examples of technologies"},{"time":421000,"text":"that are in each one of these periods."},{"time":424000,"text":"But I think that the implications of them approaching"},{"time":427000,"text":"these crossovers, these intersections, are interesting to think about."}]},{"cues":[{"time":430000,"text":"Start with gene sequencing."},{"time":432000,"text":"As you probably know, gene sequencing -- in a large part,"},{"time":435000,"text":"because it's built on computers -- is falling in price"},{"time":438000,"text":"at a kind of a Moore's Law-like level."},{"time":440000,"text":"It is now possible -- will be possible,"},{"time":443000,"text":"and if Craig Venter indeed comes today,"},{"time":446000,"text":"he may tell you something about this --"},{"time":447000,"text":"to sequence the human genome for 40 million dollars by the end of this year."},{"time":452000,"text":"That's as opposed to billions just a few years ago."},{"time":457000,"text":"You know, our ability to capture the tools of creation"},{"time":462000,"text":"is getting closer and closer."}]},{"cues":[{"time":464000,"text":"What's interesting is that at the same time, the number of genes"},{"time":467000,"text":"that we're discovering is rising very quickly."},{"time":469000,"text":"Each one of these genes has potential diagnostic test."},{"time":472000,"text":"There will come a day"},{"time":474000,"text":"when you can have hundreds of thousands of tests done, very cheaply,"},{"time":478000,"text":"if you want to know. You can learn about your own mosaic."}]},{"cues":[{"time":483000,"text":"Here's another technology that's approaching a critical price."},{"time":486000,"text":"This is a fascinating research from WHO that shows the effect"},{"time":490000,"text":"of generic drugs on anti-retroviral drug compounds and cocktails."},{"time":497000,"text":"In January 2000, the price was 10,000 dollars, or 27 dollars a day."},{"time":503000,"text":"The generics came in, first in Brazil and elsewhere,"},{"time":506000,"text":"and the effect was just dramatic on pricing."},{"time":510000,"text":"Today it's less than 50 cents a day."},{"time":515000,"text":"And what's interesting is if you look at the price elasticity,"},{"time":520000,"text":"if you look at the correlation between these two,"},{"time":523000,"text":"as the anti-retrovirals come down, the number of people you can treat"},{"time":526000,"text":"goes radically up. And the Clinton Foundation and WHO"},{"time":532000,"text":"believe that they can treat three million people worldwide by 2005 --"},{"time":536000,"text":"two million in sub-Saharan Africa."},{"time":538000,"text":"And the falling price of drugs has a lot to do with that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541000,"text":"Linux is another good example."},{"time":543000,"text":"Now we've switched to critical mass."},{"time":545000,"text":"These are now technologies that are hitting critical mass."},{"time":547000,"text":"If you look here, here's Linux in red, and it's hit 20 percent."},{"time":553000,"text":"Interestingly, it's done a crossover before,"},{"time":555000,"text":"but not the crossovers that matter."},{"time":557000,"text":"The crossover that's going to matter is the one with the blue."},{"time":560000,"text":"But you can look and see the direction those lines are going,"},{"time":562000,"text":"you can see that at the 20 percent, it's now taken seriously."},{"time":565000,"text":"It's not just for the geeks any more."},{"time":569000,"text":"That is, I imagine, what people in Redmond"},{"time":571000,"text":"wake up in the middle of the night thinking about."},{"time":573000,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":575000,"text":"Another technology that we see all around us out here is hybrid cars."},{"time":579000,"text":"I don't know whether anybody has a Prius 2004, but they're fantastic."},{"time":582000,"text":"And if you look at the trends here, by about 2008 --"},{"time":586000,"text":"and I don't think this is a crazy forecast --"},{"time":588000,"text":"they'll be two percent of auto sales."},{"time":590000,"text":"Two percent isn't 20 percent, but in the car business,"},{"time":593000,"text":"which is slow moving, that's huge; that's arrival."},{"time":599000,"text":"At two percent, you start seeing them on the roads everywhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":602000,"text":"And what's interesting about the hybrids taking off"},{"time":606000,"text":"is you've now introduced electric motors to the automobile industry."},{"time":610000,"text":"It's the first radical change in automobile technology in 100 years."},{"time":614000,"text":"And once you have electric motors, you can do anything:"},{"time":617000,"text":"you can change the structure of the car in any way you want."},{"time":620000,"text":"You can have regenerative braking; you can have drive-by-wire;"},{"time":623000,"text":"you can have replaceable body shapes --"},{"time":625000,"text":"it's a little thing that starts with a hybrid,"},{"time":627000,"text":"but it can lead to a whole new era of the car."}]},{"cues":[{"time":630000,"text":"Voice Over IP is something you may have heard something about."},{"time":633000,"text":"Again, it's kind of coming out of nowhere;"},{"time":634000,"text":"it's a little hard to use right now."},{"time":636000,"text":"There's a company created by the Kazaa founders called Skype."},{"time":640000,"text":"Look at these numbers. They launched it in August of last year;"},{"time":643000,"text":"they already have nearly four million registered users --"},{"time":648000,"text":"that's critical mass."},{"time":651000,"text":"And the same thing's happening on the carrier side."},{"time":654000,"text":"You're looking at IP taking over from some of the traditional"},{"time":658000,"text":"telecom standards. This is a tipping point --"},{"time":662000,"text":"if Malcolm's here, forgive me -- and it's going to change the economics,"},{"time":666000,"text":"and the speed, and the players in the industry."},{"time":670000,"text":"It's going to look a little bit like that."}]},{"cues":[{"time":676000,"text":"And finally, free. Free is really, really interesting."},{"time":682000,"text":"Free is something that comes with digital, because"},{"time":688000,"text":"the reproduction costs are essentially free. It comes with IP,"},{"time":694000,"text":"because it's such an efficient protocol. It comes with fiber optics,"},{"time":697000,"text":"because there's so much bandwidth."},{"time":698000,"text":"Free is really, you know, the gift of Silicon Valley to the world."},{"time":703000,"text":"It's an economic force; it's a technical force."},{"time":706000,"text":"It's a deflationary force, if not handled right."},{"time":710000,"text":"It is abundance, as opposed to scarcity."},{"time":713000,"text":"Free is probably the most interesting thing."}]},{"cues":[{"time":715000,"text":"And here you have just the number of songs"},{"time":718000,"text":"that can be stored on a hard drive."},{"time":720000,"text":"You know, there could be a film's [unclear] there,"},{"time":724000,"text":"but it's basically, every song ever made could be stored"},{"time":727000,"text":"on 400 dollars worth of storage by 2008. It takes that entire element,"},{"time":734000,"text":"the physical element, of songs off the table."},{"time":738000,"text":"And you've seen the numbers."},{"time":739000,"text":"I mean, you know, the music industry is imploding"},{"time":743000,"text":"in front of our very eyes, and Hollywood's worried as well."},{"time":746000,"text":"They're facing a force that they haven't faced before."},{"time":751000,"text":"And their response is draconian, and not necessarily"},{"time":758000,"text":"the one that's going to get them out of this."}]},{"cues":[{"time":762000,"text":"And finally, I'll give you one last example of free --"},{"time":765000,"text":"perhaps the most powerful of all. I mentioned fiber optics --"},{"time":768000,"text":"their abundance tends to make things free."},{"time":770000,"text":"This is the price of a phone call to India per minute."},{"time":774000,"text":"And what's interesting is that it was just 1990"},{"time":777000,"text":"when it was more than two dollars a minute."},{"time":780000,"text":"India had, still has, a regulated phone system and so did we."},{"time":788000,"text":"It was surprisingly non-innovative, moved very slowly,"},{"time":793000,"text":"but then there was just so much fiber out there,"},{"time":796000,"text":"you couldn't hold back, and look how quickly the price fell."},{"time":800000,"text":"It's seven cents a minute, in many cases."}]},{"cues":[{"time":804000,"text":"And the consequence of cheap phone calling, free phone calling,"},{"time":809000,"text":"to India, is the pissed-off programmer, is the outsourcing."},{"time":814000,"text":"It is probably one of the most dramatic shifts in globalization"},{"time":818000,"text":"and one of the most powerful economic tools"},{"time":821000,"text":"that we're seeing in our world today."},{"time":822000,"text":"The force of India, and then China, and any other country"},{"time":827000,"text":"that can contact our markets"},{"time":829000,"text":"and will work with our companies -- because the communications are free --"},{"time":834000,"text":"is just beginning to be felt."},{"time":836000,"text":"And I think that's probably one"},{"time":837000,"text":"of the most important technology trends that we're looking at today."},{"time":839000,"text":"Thank you."}]}]}